  <!--   Chapter  1   -->
  <!--   **********   -->
  <chapter number="1" style="c" sid="PHP 1" />
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="1" style="v" sid="PHP 1:1" /><char style="it">From </char>Paul and Timothy, slaves of Christ Jesus,</para>
    <para style="p" vid="PHP 1:1">To all the saints (i.e., believers) in Christ Jesus who live in Philippi together with <char style="it">the
        </char>bishops (i.e., head pastors; overseers) and deacons (i.e., assistant pastors; assistants entrusted
        with significant responsibilities; heads of ministry departments):<verse eid="PHP 1:1"/>
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="2" style="v" sid="PHP 1:2" />Grace to you and peace from God our Father and <char style="it">the </char>Lord Jesus Christ.<verse eid="PHP 1:2" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="3" style="v" sid="PHP 1:3" />I give thanks to my God every time I think about you while reminiscing, <verse eid="PHP 1:3" />
      <verse number="4" style="v" sid="PHP 1:4" />always making every one of my requests put into prayer for you all with joy, <verse eid="PHP 1:4" />
      <verse number="5" style="v" sid="PHP 1:5" /><char style="it">and I give thanks </char>for your working closely <char style="it">with me</char> in
        <char style="it">the</char> <char style="it">spreading of </char>the Gospel (i.e., the good-news message
        of Christ) from the first day until the present. <verse eid="PHP 1:5" />
      <verse number="6" style="v" sid="PHP 1:6" />I’ve reached the point where I’m convinced of this very thing, that He who began a good work in you will
        complete it, <char style="it">working towards that ends</char> until <char style="it">the </char>day
        of Christ Jesus, <verse eid="PHP 1:6" />
      <verse number="7" style="v" sid="PHP 1:7" />just as it’s right for me to be thinking about all of you this way, on account of me having you both
        in my heart and in my chains and in the verbal defense and confirmation of the certainty of the Gospel—you
        all being my fellow-workers of <char style="it">this </char>grace.<verse eid="PHP 1:7" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="8" style="v" sid="PHP 1:8" />In this regard, God is my witness to the fact that I long for all you with the deep, inner affections
        of Christ Jesus. <verse eid="PHP 1:8" />
      <verse number="9" style="v" sid="PHP 1:9" />And I pray this, that your love would proliferate even more and more in recognition, in more precise
        knowledge, and in every <char style="it">sort of</char> insight gained from perception, <verse eid="PHP 1:9" />
      <verse number="10" style="v" sid="PHP 1:10" />resulting in your continual testing and approving of those things which excel, so that you would be sincere
        and won’t get tripped up <char style="it">and would maintain this </char>to <char style="it">the </char>day
        of Christ, <verse eid="PHP 1:10" />
      <verse number="11" style="v" sid="PHP 1:11" />having reached the point where you’ve been filled from the byproduct<char style="sup">[a]</char> of righteousness
        which <char style="it">is </char>through Jesus Christ to <char style="it">the</char> glory and praise
        of God.<verse eid="PHP 1:11" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="12" style="v" sid="PHP 1:12" />I want you to know, comrades<char style="sup">[b]</char>, that the situation I find myself in has further
        advanced the Gospel, <verse eid="PHP 1:12" />
      <verse number="13" style="v" sid="PHP 1:13" />in that an awareness and understanding of my bonds in Christ has been made known among the entire palace
        guard detachment and among everyone else, <verse eid="PHP 1:13" />
      <verse number="14" style="v" sid="PHP 1:14" />and many of the comrades in <char style="it">the </char>Lord, urged on by my bonds, are much more daring
        about <char style="it">going around </char>speaking the word <char style="it">of God </char>without fear.<verse eid="PHP 1:14" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="15" style="v" sid="PHP 1:15" />While <char style="it">it’s true that</char> some preach Christ because <char style="it">they’re motivated
        by</char> jealousy and strife, on the other hand some <char style="it">are motivated </char>by good intentions.<verse eid="PHP 1:15" />
      <verse number="16" style="v" sid="PHP 1:16" />While they who <char style="it">spread the Gospel </char>out of love know for a fact that I’ve been appointed
        to give a verbal defense of the Gospel, <verse eid="PHP 1:16" />
      <verse number="17" style="v" sid="PHP 1:17" />on the other hand they who proclaim Christ<char style="it"> </char>out of ambition and not with sincerity
        expect to stir up vexation <char style="it">for me </char>while I’m in jail<char style="sup">[c]</char>.<verse eid="PHP 1:17" />
      <verse number="18" style="v" sid="PHP 1:18" />So what?—except <char style="it">for this</char>: that Christ is proclaimed in all respects, whether
        with ulterior motives or with no hidden agenda<char style="sup">[d]</char>, and in this I rejoice—and
        <char style="it">indeed </char>I will rejoice, <verse eid="PHP 1:18" />
      <verse number="19" style="v" sid="PHP 1:19" />for I know for a fact that this will result in deliverance for me through your prayer and the support
        of the Spirit of Christ Jesus, <verse eid="PHP 1:19" />
      <verse number="20" style="v" sid="PHP 1:20" />in line with my eager expectation and hope that I won’t be embarrassed or humiliated in any way, but
        rather with every <char style="it">sort of</char> frankness, forthrightness, and openness <char style="it">imaginable</char>
        Christ will be magnified now—as always—in my body, whether through life or through death.<verse eid="PHP 1:20" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="21" style="v" sid="PHP 1:21" />You see, the way I see it<char style="sup">[e]</char>, to live <char style="it">is </char>Christ and
        to die is gain (i.e., is advantageous; is a desirable option). <verse eid="PHP 1:21" />
      <verse number="22" style="v" sid="PHP 1:22" />If I live on in <char style="it">the</char> flesh, this <char style="it">will yield </char>tangible results
        from <char style="it">my </char>work<char style="sup">[f]</char>. And what will I choose?—I can’t tell;<verse eid="PHP 1:22" />
      <verse number="23" style="v" sid="PHP 1:23" />I’m caught between the two, having the desire to be set free again<char style="it"> </char>and to be
        together with Christ, for <char style="it">this is </char>much, much better<char style="sup">[g]</char>.<verse eid="PHP 1:23" />
      <verse number="24" style="v" sid="PHP 1:24" />But to remain in the flesh is more necessary for your sakes. <verse eid="PHP 1:24" />
      <verse number="25" style="v" sid="PHP 1:25" />And convinced of this I know that I will remain <char style="it">here on Earth</char> and stay by your
        side—with all of you—for your progress and for <char style="it">the </char>joy <char style="it">which
        comes </char>from faith, <verse eid="PHP 1:25" />
      <verse number="26" style="v" sid="PHP 1:26" />so that your grounds for speaking proudly would proliferate in Christ Jesus by my doing, on account of
        me visiting you again.<verse eid="PHP 1:26" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="27" style="v" sid="PHP 1:27" />Only let your life in society be worthy of the Gospel of Christ, so that, whether I come and see you
        or am away, I hear what you’re up to, that you stand <char style="it">together</char> in one spirit<char
        style="sup">[h]</char>, one soul, joined together by the Faith of the Gospel <verse eid="PHP 1:27" />
      <verse number="28" style="v" sid="PHP 1:28" />and are not frightened and intimidated by anything <char style="it">done </char>by <char style="it">your</char>
        adversaries, which in particular is indicative of their ruin, but of your salvation (i.e., your being
        kept from ruin); and this <char style="it">intimidation-ruin-salvation pattern is</char> from God, <verse eid="PHP 1:28" />
      <verse number="29" style="v" sid="PHP 1:29" />since the thing given—undeservedly so<char style="sup">[i]</char>—to you on Christ’s behalf is to not
        only to believe in him but to suffer on his behalf, <verse eid="PHP 1:29" />
      <verse number="30" style="v" sid="PHP 1:30" />having the same anguish and conflict <char style="it">as he did</char>, the very thing you saw <char
        style="it">happening </char>to and in me and now hear reports <char style="it">are happening </char>to
        and in me.<verse eid="PHP 1:30" />
    </para>
