  <chapter number="2" style="c" sid="PHP 2" />
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="1" style="v" sid="PHP 2:1" />So now, if <char style="it">there’s</char> any comfort or exhortation in Christ, if any consolation offered
        by love, if any commonality and fellowship of spirit<char style="sup">[a]</char>, if any deep, inner
        affection— <verse eid="PHP 2:1" />
      <verse number="2" style="v" sid="PHP 2:2" />you’ll make me overjoyed if you would adopt that way of thinking<char style="sup">[b]</char>, having
        the same love, being harmonious and on the same page<char style="sup">[c]</char>, <verse eid="PHP 2:2" />
      <verse number="3" style="v" sid="PHP 2:3" /><char style="it">with </char>no one motivated by ambition or by conceit but by humility instead, considering
        each other to be better than yourselves, <verse eid="PHP 2:3" />
      <verse number="4" style="v" sid="PHP 2:4" />not paying careful attention to your own affairs <char style="it">exclusively </char>but instead <char
        style="it">paying careful attention </char>to each other’s affairs as well.<verse eid="PHP 2:4" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="5" style="v" sid="PHP 2:5" />Maintain in you the way of thinking that was also in Christ Jesus, <verse eid="PHP 2:5" />
      <verse number="6" style="v" sid="PHP 2:6" />who, while existing in <char style="it">the</char> form of God, didn’t think being equal to God was <char
        style="it">a thing</char> <char style="it">that had to be </char>to be held onto with everything you’ve
        got<char style="sup">[d]</char>, <verse eid="PHP 2:6" />
      <verse number="7" style="v" sid="PHP 2:7" />but instead depleted himself and assumed the form of a slave, having turned into something similar to
        humans, and, unveiled to the public<char style="sup">[e]</char> having the appearance of that of a human
        being, <verse eid="PHP 2:7" />
      <verse number="8" style="v" sid="PHP 2:8" />he humbled himself and became obedient until <char style="it">it reached a point where the obedience
        required his </char>death, <char style="it">not just any-old death </char>but <char style="it">the </char>death
        of <char style="it">crucifixion on</char> a cross. <verse eid="PHP 2:8" />
      <verse number="9" style="v" sid="PHP 2:9" />And in light of this, God<char style="sup">[A]</char> exalted him (i.e., promoted him to a high position)
        and <char style="it">out of His generosity </char>gave<char style="sup">[B]</char> him the name which
        is above all names (i.e., gave him the ultimate top rank, outranking every other rank), <verse eid="PHP 2:9" />
      <verse number="10" style="v" sid="PHP 2:10" />so that in the name of Jesus (i.e. when Jesus’s authority is invoked) every knee would bow of <char style="it">the
        things in the</char> heavens (i.e., in heaven; in the spiritual domain) and of <char style="it">the things</char>
        on the Earth and of <char style="it">the things</char> under the earth (i.e., the world of the dead,
        including hell) <verse eid="PHP 2:10" />
      <verse number="11" style="v" sid="PHP 2:11" />and every tongue <char style="it">would </char>confess out loud that Jesus Christ is Lord to <char style="it">the
        </char>glory of God <char style="it">the </char>Father.<verse eid="PHP 2:11" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="12" style="v" sid="PHP 2:12" />So now, my dear <char style="it">comrades</char>, just as you have always obeyed, not just when I was
        there in person but even more in my absence, work at the salvation where your own selves are concerned
        with the utmost reverence and respect<char style="sup">[f]</char>; <verse eid="PHP 2:12" />
      <verse number="13" style="v" sid="PHP 2:13" />you see, God is the One Who’s working in you both the wanting and the working-on of what pleases Him<char
        style="sup">[g]</char>.<verse eid="PHP 2:13" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="14" style="v" sid="PHP 2:14" />Do all things while distancing yourselves from grumbling and scheming or plotting, <verse eid="PHP 2:14" />
      <verse number="15" style="v" sid="PHP 2:15" />so that you would become blameless and innocent, children of God in the midst of a crooked and perverted
        Zeitgeist<char style="sup">[h]</char>, in which you shine as lights in <char style="it">the </char>world,<verse eid="PHP 2:15" />
      <verse number="16" style="v" sid="PHP 2:16" />holding fast to a message of life, resulting in me having proud words to tell others <char style="it">up</char>
        to the day of Christ, since you haven’t run <char style="it">life’s race </char>or toiled for nothing.<verse eid="PHP 2:16" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="17" style="v" sid="PHP 2:17" />Anyways, if I’m being poured out <char style="it">like a libation</char> upon the altar and <char style="it">during
        the</char> liturgy of your faith, I will rejoice and will rejoice together<char style="sup">[i]</char>
        with you all— <verse eid="PHP 2:17" />
      <verse number="18" style="v" sid="PHP 2:18" />And the same <char style="it">for you</char>: you will rejoice and will rejoice together with me.<verse eid="PHP 2:18" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="19" style="v" sid="PHP 2:19" />Now I hope in <char style="it">the </char>Lord Jesus to send Timothy to you posthaste, so that once I
        know what you’re up to, it’ll put me at ease. <verse eid="PHP 2:19" />
      <verse number="20" style="v" sid="PHP 2:20" />I have no one, you see, who sees things the way I do, a certain someone who’ll truly care for you. <verse eid="PHP 2:20" />
      <verse number="21" style="v" sid="PHP 2:21" />In fact, everyone <char style="it">I’ve tried to find to work with me </char>is pursuing their own self-interests,
        not the interests of Jesus Christ. <verse eid="PHP 2:21" />
      <verse number="22" style="v" sid="PHP 2:22" />But you’re familiar with how he qualified <char style="it">to receive my trust</char>, that he served
        me in the Gospel like a son serves a father. <verse eid="PHP 2:22" />
      <verse number="23" style="v" sid="PHP 2:23" />So I certainly hope to send this <char style="it">fellow</char> as I could immediately turn my attention
        to my affairs <char style="it">were he to be sent</char>. <verse eid="PHP 2:23" />
      <verse number="24" style="v" sid="PHP 2:24" />I’m convinced in <char style="it">the </char>Lord of the same, that I too will come posthaste.<verse eid="PHP 2:24" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="25" style="v" sid="PHP 2:25" />I deemed it necessary that I send you Epaphroditus, my comrade<char style="sup">[j]</char>, coworker,
        and fellow soldier-in-arms—your missionary<char style="sup">[k]</char> and my personal attendant— <verse eid="PHP 2:25" />
      <verse number="26" style="v" sid="PHP 2:26" />since he was longing <char style="it">to see </char>all of you and was quite distressed because you heard
        that he was rundown with some sort of sickness<char style="sup">[l]</char>. <verse eid="PHP 2:26" />
      <verse number="27" style="v" sid="PHP 2:27" />You see, he was weakened by sickness to the point of death, but instead <char style="it">of him dying
        </char>God had mercy on him, and not just on him but on me too so that I wouldn’t be wrenched with pain
        upon pain. <verse eid="PHP 2:27" />
      <verse number="28" style="v" sid="PHP 2:28" />So with even more urgency I sent him <char style="it">on his way </char>so that after seeing him again
        you would rejoice and I would be relieved of my pain. <verse eid="PHP 2:28" />
      <verse number="29" style="v" sid="PHP 2:29" />So receive him in <char style="it">the </char>Lord with all <char style="it">the</char> joy <char style="it">you
        can muster,</char> and honor<char style="sup">[m]</char> individuals like him, <verse eid="PHP 2:29" />
      <verse number="30" style="v" sid="PHP 2:30" />since he came close to death on account of Christ’s work, risking <char style="it">his </char>very life
        so that he would fill in the gap caused by your drop-off in serving me.<verse eid="PHP 2:30" />
    </para>
