    <note caller="[f]" style="f">
      <char style="fk">[f]</char>
      <char style="ft"><char style="it">a</char>…Or: <char style="it">the</char></char>
      <char style="fp"></char>
    </note>
    <note caller="[A]" style="f">
      <char style="fk">[A]</char>
      <char style="ft"><char style="it">the circumcision</char>…Many biblical scholars believe that the Philippian church consisted
        of all women. If this is the case, then Paul is calling women “the circumcision,” which, physically speaking,
        only applies to men. This supports the notion that there are words in the Bible which, on the surface
        only apply to men, but in fact apply to both men and women.</char>
    </note>
